es at $x/D \\gtrsim 30$.\nOverall, we find that the coherence of wakes, initiated by the VS mode at the\nbody, is prolonged by buoyancy to far downstream. Also, this coherence is\nspatially modified by buoyancy into horizontal layers and IGWs. Low-order\ntruncations of SPOD modes are shown to efficiently reconstruct important\nsecond-order statistics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 May 2021 06:00:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Dec 2021 21:53:54 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-02"}
