npair as a function of $\\beta$. Second, we revisit the classical study of toral\nautomorphisms in our framework, and in particular for the classical \"golden\nmean\" toral automorphism we explicitly compute the kernel of the standard\npresentation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 14 May 2021 11:24:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-17"}
